                    </div>
                    <span>I bought the last 2 versions of Leo Laporte's TechTV book (I even have the one where they misspelled "Almanac" on the cover!) and have been a big fan. But, I have been reading PC Magazine longer than I have Leo's books, and when I discovered this little gem I was very excited.<P>The PC Magazine Technology Almanac is jam-packed with tips, tricks, and insider information that I can actually use. And I know I am supposed to read it a day at a time, but I find I am already up to March of next year!<P>And the best part is that is comes with a free subscription to the magazine, so I was able to renew for free! How can you loose?<P>If you, like me, have been buying Leo's book, take a look at this one from PC Magazine. It is absolutely the better of the 2, and is full of stuff you can really use.<P>Sorry Leo, but I switched!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">I'm already looking forward to the 2005 edition!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
